        "tag": "p",
        "kind": "paragraph",
        "text": "nginx (\" engine x \") is an HTTP web server, reverse proxy, content cache, load balancer, TCP/UDP proxy server, and mail proxy server. Originally written by Igor Sysoev and distributed under the 2-clause BSD License . Enterprise distributions, commercial support and training are available from F5, Inc.",
        "depth": 3
      },
      {
        "path": "/div[1]/div[2]/p[2]",
        "tag": "p",
        "kind": "paragraph",
        "text": "Docs • Code • Install • Beginner's Guide",
        "depth": 3
      },
      {
        "path": "/div[1]/div[2]/center[1]/h4[1]",
        "tag": "h4",
        "kind": "heading",
        "text": "Latest News",
        "depth": 4,
        "heading_level": 4
      },
      {
        "path": "/div[1]/div[2]/table[1]/tbody[1]/tr[1]/td[1]",
        "tag": "td",
        "kind": "table_cell",
        "text": "2026-03-24",
        "depth": 6
      },
      {
        "path": "/div[1]/div[2]/table[1]/tbody[1]/tr[1]/td[2]",
        "tag": "td",
        "kind": "table_cell",
        "text": "nginx-1.28.3 stable and nginx-1.29.7 mainline versions have been released, with fixes for buffer overflow vulnerability in the ngx_http_dav_module (CVE-2026-27654), buffer overflow vulnerabilities in the ngx_http_mp4_module (CVE-2026-27784, CVE-2026-32647), mail session authentication vulnerabilities (CVE-2026-27651, CVE-2026-28753) and OCSP result bypass vulnerability in stream (CVE-2026-28755). Additionally, nginx-1.29.7 mainline version introduces support for Multipath TCP and upgrades the default proxy HTTP version to HTTP/1.1 with keep-alive enabled .",
        "depth": 6
      },
      {
        "path": "/div[1]/div[2]/table[1]/tbody[1]/tr[1]/td[2]/p[1]",
        "tag": "p",
        "kind": "paragraph",
        "text": "nginx-1.28.3 stable and nginx-1.29.7 mainline versions have been released, with fixes for buffer overflow vulnerability in the ngx_http_dav_module (CVE-2026-27654), buffer overflow vulnerabilities in the ngx_http_mp4_module (CVE-2026-27784, CVE-2026-32647), mail session authentication vulnerabilities (CVE-2026-27651, CVE-2026-28753) and OCSP result bypass vulnerability in stream (CVE-2026-28755). Additionally, nginx-1.29.7 mainline version introduces support for Multipath TCP and upgrades the default proxy HTTP version to HTTP/1.1 with keep-alive enabled .",
        "depth": 7
      },
      {
        "path": "/div[1]/div[2]/table[1]/tbody[1]/tr[2]/td[1]",
